<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>31-1372.11</num>
  <heading>Policy loans.</heading>
  <text>A life insurer may lend to a policyholder on the security of the cash surrender value of the policyholder’s policy a sum not exceeding the legal reserve that the insurer is required to maintain on the policy.</text>
  <annotations>
